Diagnosis.
This new species can be distinguished from all the other species of this subgenus by the combination of the following characters: (
1
) 
5
th tarsomere with setae beneath; (
2
) pronotum cordiform, basal margin narrower than or subequal to the anterior margin (

Fig. 
7

); (
3
) pronotum lateral margins with one seta on each side; (
4
) median lobe of aedeagus with apical lamella long, strongly bent to the left in dorsal view (

Fig. 
31

); (
5
) right paramere long and bent, apex sharp (

Fig. 
71

B).

Distribution . Only known form the type locality, Tiechanghuang (Hubei) (
Fig. 110
).
